documentation.div:
If the JobScheduler fails to send mails, for example, because the mail server is down, then these mails will be stored in a special mail directory. This job tries to send the mails that have been stored in this directory.
This job can be triggered by orders or executed as a standard job. As a standard job, all files in the stored mails directory are processed;
as an order driven job, all files for a recipient are sent as one mail.
